<div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-8">
  <div class="lg:col-span-2">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3 tracking-tight">Love Compatibility Calculator</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8 leading-relaxed">How well do you and your crush match? Enter both names and instantly see your love compatibility percentage based on classic name numerology — fun, fast, and shareable.</p>

    <div class="mb-8"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "leaderboard" %></div>

    <div data-controller="love-compatibility-calculator ad-engagement" class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 md:gap-8">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <label class="block text-sm font-semibold text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1.5">Your name</label>
            <input type="text" data-love-compatibility-calculator-target="name1" data-action="input->love-compatibility-calculator#calculate" class="w-full" value="Alex" placeholder="Your name">
          </div>
          <div>
            <label class="block text-sm font-semibold text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1.5">Their name</label>
            <input type="text" data-love-compatibility-calculator-target="name2" data-action="input->love-compatibility-calculator#calculate" class="w-full" value="Sam" placeholder="Their name">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true" class="bg-gradient-to-br from-pink-50 to-rose-50 dark:from-pink-900/20 dark:to-rose-900/20 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-5">Love Match</h2>
          <div class="text-center mb-4">
            <div class="text-5xl font-extrabold text-pink-700 dark:text-pink-400" data-love-compatibility-calculator-target="resultPercent">—</div>
            <div class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-2" data-love-compatibility-calculator-target="resultLabel">—</div>
          </div>
          <div class="w-full bg-pink-100 dark:bg-pink-900/30 rounded-full h-3 overflow-hidden">
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-500 to-rose-500 h-full transition-all duration-500" style="width: 0%" data-love-compatibility-calculator-target="resultBar"></div>
          </div>
          <button data-action="click->love-compatibility-calculator#copy" class="mt-6 w-full px-4 py-2.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-600 to-rose-600 hover:from-pink-700 hover:to-rose-700 text-white rounded-xl shadow-sm transition-all duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-pink-500 focus:ring-offset-2 text-sm font-medium">Copy Result</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <%= render "shared/calculator_rating", slug: "love-compatibility-calculator" %>
    <div class="mb-8"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "in_results" %></div>

    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>How the Love Compatibility Calculator Works</h2>
      <p>
        The calculator turns each letter of both names into its position in the alphabet (A=1, B=2, all the way to Z=26), sums the two name totals together, and runs that sum through a simple formula to land on a percentage between 40 and 99. Numerology has been used for love-matching for centuries, and even though it has no scientific basis, the math is consistent — you will always get the same percentage for the same two names. Use the result as a fun ice-breaker, a shareable Instagram story, or a playful way to bring up the topic with someone you like.
      </p>

      <div class="my-6"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "in_content" %></div>

      <h2>What Your Score Means (and Doesn't)</h2>
      <p>
        A score of 90 or higher gets the "Soulmates" label, 75–89 is an "Excellent match", 60–74 is "Good match", 50–59 is "Could work", and below 50 is "Needs effort". These are entertainment labels — they have zero predictive value for whether your relationship will succeed. Real relationship outcomes depend on attachment style, communication patterns, shared goals, and how you handle conflict. The Gottman Institute's research over 40+ years shows that the four "horsemen" (criticism, contempt, defensiveness, stonewalling) predict divorce far more reliably than any number on a calculator.
      </p>

      <h2>Why Numerology Calculators Are Still Fun</h2>
      <p>
        Even though the science is zero, the cultural appeal is real. Love calculators have existed since at least the 1990s, when MASH (a classroom paper game) was the dominant version, and FLAMES followed shortly after. They give people permission to talk about feelings indirectly — "the calculator says we're 87% compatible" is much easier to say at 14 than "I like you". Adults still use them as conversation starters on dates, in group chats, and for content. The fun is in the result, not the accuracy.
      </p>

      <h2>What Actually Predicts Relationship Success</h2>
      <p>
        Researchers consistently find five factors that correlate with lasting relationships: shared values (especially around money, kids, and how to spend time), similar attachment styles or at least secure attachment in both partners, the ability to repair after conflict, friendship as the foundation, and matched effort. None of those show up in a name calculator. If you want a more useful self-assessment, look up the 36 questions to fall in love (a Stony Brook research instrument), the Gottman 7 Principles, or the Five Love Languages quiz.
      </p>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>Should I use my full name or nickname?</h3>
      <p>Try both. The result will be different, and there's no "right" version — pick whichever name feels most like you in the relationship.</p>

      <h3>Can I calculate compatibility with a celebrity?</h3>
      <p>Of course. Try your name with your favorite singer, actor, or athlete — that's exactly what these calculators are for.</p>

      <h3>Why don't I get 100%?</h3>
      <p>The formula caps at 99% on purpose — a 100% score would feel suspicious and a 0% score would feel mean.</p>

      <h3>Is this the same as a zodiac compatibility test?</h3>
      <p>No — zodiac tests use birth signs, not names. Both are entertainment, but they use completely different methods.</p>

      <h3>Can I share the result?</h3>
      <p>Yes — click the Copy Result button and paste it into any chat, story, or social post.</p>

      <%= render "shared/print_button" %>
      <%= render "shared/calculation_email_capture" %>
    </article>

